  "prompt": "What is the significance of the black dot symbol with reference to the Nirbhaya case?",
  "response": "In the Nirbhaya case, the black dot symbol became associated with the case as a symbol of protest and solidarity against sexual violence. After the horrific gang rape and murder of Jyoti Singh (Nirbhaya) in Delhi in December 2012, the black dot came to represent the collective outrage and demand for justice and systemic changes to address violence against women in India. The symbol was used in various protests, social media campaigns, and awareness efforts to highlight the urgent need for women's safety and legal reforms.",
